                     <roleName type="title">ʾAto</roleName> Walda ʾAragāwi is mentioned as the donor in Additio 1 and in the supplication formula on <locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>.&#xD;
Also his family members are mentioned.</persName>
                  <!--ACHTUNG! This is actually paragraphic information identifying the donor. 
                                        Person/persName should only contain the person name, not all the paragraph.-->
               </person>
               <person>
                  <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS00000">Wagris</persName>
               </person>
               <person>
                  <persName role="owner" ref="PRS0000">The first owner of the Ms. was probably King Yoḥannǝs I (r. 1667-82) since his name, his mother’s (?) name ʾƎḫǝtä Krǝstos and his wife’s name Säblä Wängel are mentioned in the headings of the Gospel of Mark (s. <locus target="#52rb">52rb</locus>), Luke (<locus target="#81rb">81rb</locus>) and John (<locus target="#134rb">134rb</locus>). Probably, their names were also written in the heading of the Mathews Gospel but later erased (<locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>) in order to write down the name of the later donor, <roleName type="title">ʾato</roleName> Walda ʾAragāwi.&#xD;
Another possibility is that the commissioner of the Ms. only wished to mention the name of the ruler.  &#xD;
Later, the Ms. belonged to the church of Mäqdäla Madḫāne ʿĀlam.</persName>
                  <!--ACHTUNG! This is actually paragraphic information identifying the donor. 
                                        Person/persName should only contain the person name, not all the paragraph.-->
               </person>
